        </p>
        <h4 style='margin-left:10px; margin-bottom:15px'> What's Going On? </h4>
        <p style='margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px;'>
            Images are randomly selected from a database a displayed on the homepage.
            As a member of society it is your job to decide if what's depected is male
            or female by clicking on the arrows.
        </p>
        <p style='margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px;'>
            Images that are declared male by the majority of society are displayed
            on the <%= link_to 'Manpage', person_path('manpage')%>.
            </br>
            Images that are declared female by the majority of society are displayed
            on the <%= link_to 'Fempage', person_path('fempage')%>. 
            </br>
            What happens to an image that is evenly voted a man and woman?
            Nonsense that would never happen.
        </p>
        <h4 style='margin-left:10px; margin-bottom:15px'>Okay, But Why?</h4>
        <p style='margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px;'>
            Well this is technically an "art piece" created for my Art and Activism class.
            So I encourage you to interact with the website yourself and derive
            your own meanings from my silly website. Plus, the website can
            gain new meaning based on how people interact with it. But, incase it wasn't clear this
            is a satire on traditional societal views on gender.
        </p>
    </div>
